fix: remove clippy::await_holding_lock warnings in tests
Replace std::sync::Mutex with tokio::sync::Mutex in test isolation mechanism to resolve clippy warnings. This change improves async compatibility and follows Rust async best practices while maintaining test isolation functionality.
Changes: - Replace std::sync::Mutex with tokio::sync::Mutex in TEST_MUTEX - Remove #[allow(clippy::await_holding_lock)] annotations - Update lock usage from .unwrap() to .await for async compatibility - Preserve test isolation to prevent environment variable conflicts
Files modified: - tests/match_cache_reuse_tests.rs: Updated mutex implementation - .github/codex/115-clippy-await-holding-lock-warning-fix-report.md: Added work report
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: add code review report for Backlog #27 Wiremock integration testing framework
Comprehensive code review evaluation of the Wiremock integration testing framework implementation (Backlog #27). The review covers:
- Complete functional requirements fulfillment - High-quality code implementation (8.3/10 overall score) - Excellent architectural design with proper separation of concerns - Comprehensive test coverage (77.62%, exceeding 75% threshold) - Successful elimination of external OpenAI API dependencies - Significant performance improvements in test execution speed - Proper bug fixes and stability enhancements
Key achievements: - Zero external service dependencies and API costs - Complete test isolation with mutex-based serialization - Support for multiple test scenarios (success, error, delayed responses) - Modular design with MockOpenAITestHelper and MatchResponseGenerator - Performance testing with load scenarios and memory stability validation
Recommendation: Approve for merge and adopt as standard integration testing framework for SubX project. Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix(cache): resolve Wiremock integration test cache reuse issues
- Fix cache reuse test failures in both copy and move modes - Implement proper test isolation using static mutex for environment variables - Ensure each test uses dedicated cache paths to prevent interference - Modify get_cache_file_path to support XDG_CONFIG_HOME for testing - Add debug logging for cache validation (later cleaned up) - Resolve file ID mismatch issues between mock expectations and actual IDs - Clean up compilation warnings with #[allow(dead_code)] annotations
The cache logic now correctly preserves operations across multiple calls, reducing unnecessary AI API requests when directory snapshots and configuration hashes match. Tests now pass consistently in both isolated and parallel execution scenarios.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix: correct copy mode implementation in match command
Fix critical logic error in copy mode where original files were incorrectly renamed, violating copy operation semantics.
Changes: - Replace execute_copy_then_rename with execute_copy_operation - Add execute_local_copy for same-directory copy operations - Ensure original files remain unchanged in copy mode - Update test expectations to match correct copy semantics
Copy mode now properly: - Creates copies at target locations without modifying originals - Preserves original file names and locations - Only copies content, never renames source files
Resolves the core issue in Bug #16 where copy mode violated its semantic contract by modifying source files.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: add code review report for Bug #16 fix
Add comprehensive code review report analyzing the implementation of Bug #16 fix for match command cache reuse and copy mode issues.
Key findings: - Cache reuse mechanism correctly fixed - Copy mode logic contains critical error that violates copy semantics - Tests are ignored and cannot validate the fix - Immediate attention needed for copy mode implementation
The review identifies that while cache reuse was properly implemented, the copy mode still incorrectly renames original files, contradicting the copy operation semantics.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

- Add comprehensive analysis of all existing match-related integration tests - Include modification instructions for 4 test files that currently depend on real OpenAI services - Categorize test files into those requiring refactoring vs those already using mocks - Update implementation checklist to reflect actual codebase state - Provide detailed step-by-step refactoring instructions for each affected test file - Clarify that existing tests need modification, not creation of new test files

docs: accelerate API testing with modular Wiremock integration
- Add a comprehensive plan to implement a Wiremock-based integration testing framework for simulating the OpenAI API. - Outline technical design for modular mock server helpers, data generators, and test macros to enable isolated, controllable, and fast tests. - Propose step-by-step implementation phases, including infrastructure setup, test refactoring, advanced scenarios, performance, and stability testing. - Specify required extensions to test configuration and mock helpers for error handling, delayed responses, and parallelism. - Include detailed checklists for must-have and optional improvements, ensuring test isolation, resource cleanup, and backward compatibility. - Quantify expected benefits such as test speedup, cost elimination, and improved reliability, with qualitative gains for developer experience and CI/CD stability. - Address risk assessment and mitigation strategies, and define clear completion criteria for the migration to mock-based testing. - Suggest future directions for expanding the mock framework to other AI providers and automated performance/error testing.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

fix(matcher): support cache reuse in copy mode for match command
Updates core matcher cache and engine to properly reuse cache entries when using the copy mode in the match command. Adds tests to cover cache reuse and copy behavior, and includes the work report for bug fix 16.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

docs: add bug fix plan for match command cache and copy mode issues
This comprehensive bug fix plan addresses two critical issues in the match command:
1. Cache reuse ignoring copy/move parameters - When using cached dry-run results, the system incorrectly skips copy/move operations and only performs renaming.
2. Copy mode incorrectly renaming source files - In copy mode, the original subtitle files are being renamed instead of being preserved as expected.
The plan includes detailed root cause analysis, specific code fixes for the cache reuse logic and copy operation flow, comprehensive testing strategy, and implementation timeline with risk mitigation measures.
Key fixes: - Enhance cache reuse logic to recalculate relocation requirements - Implement separate copy-then-rename operation flow - Add comprehensive unit and integration tests - Establish clear acceptance criteria and delivery timeline
This addresses user-reported issues with the match command's copy functionality and ensures reliable behavior across different execution modes.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>
